line_1: Tho' Scandal would OUR PATRIOT's name impeach,
line_2: And rails at virtues which she cannot reach,

line_1: And prayed her that she might not so impeach
line_2: Gently approaching then with fairest speech

line_1: MURPHY, if not rewarded, will impeach.
line_2: Expect no mercy; facts, well grounded, teach,

line_1: And Honour, which not malice can impeach?
line_2: Of Virtue far above temptation's Reach,
Atheism and Blasphemy have dar'd to Preach,
Stiffling that Zeal, which first Themselves to the rude World did. Teach.
Define that Prudence which you Teach;
I fear 'tis much above your Learning's Reach.
